oFiles)\\n  - ENDED + TurnStart → ACTIVE (ActionClearEndedAt)\\n\\n### 2. Shadow Branch Visualization (Interactive Timeline)\\n- Show a main branch with commits\\n- Show a shadow branch named `entire/<commit-hash[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>` forking off\\n- User can click \\\"Save Step\\\" to add checkpoint commits to shadow branch\\n- Each checkpoint commit shows: file state snapshot + metadata directory\\n- Shadow branch metadata structure:\\n  ```\\n  .entire/metadata/<session-id>/\\n  ├── full.jsonl\\n  ├── prompt.txt\\n  └── tasks/<tool-use-id>/\\n  ```\\n- Show deduplication: if tree matches previous, skip the write\\n\\n### 3. Condensation Flow (Animated)\\n- User clicks \\\"Git Commit\\\" to trigger condensation\\n- Animate: data flows from shadow branch → metadata branch (entire/checkpoints/v1)\\n- Show the 12-hex-char checkpoint ID being generated\\n- Show sharded directory structure: `<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/`\\n- Show metadata.json with session_ids, session_count\\n- Show the Entire-Checkpoint trailer being added to user commit\\n- Multi-session: show how a second session adds numbered subfolder\\n\\n### 4. Rewind Visualization\\n- Show a list of rewind points from shadow branch\\n- User clicks a rewind point\\n- Animate: files restored from checkpoint tree (not git reset)\\n- Show FilesToRestore, FilesToDelete, TrackedChanges preview\\n\\n### 5. Checkpoint ID Linking (Bidirectional)\\n- Show user commit with Entire-Checkpoint trailer\\n- Show metadata branch with sharded directory\\n- Animate bidirectional lookup:\\n  - User commit → extract trailer → find metadata\\n  - Metadata → search commits → find user commit\\n\\n## Design\\n- Dark theme, modern look\\n- Use SVG or canvas for branch visualizations\\n- Smooth animations for transitions\\n- Step-by-step walkthrough mode with \\\"Next\\\" button\\n- Each section should be independently explorable\\n- Include brief explanatory text for each concept\\n- Color coding: shadow branch (purple), metadata branch (gre